    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "calling a counselor or talking to my parents just makes it real. right now, it's like i'm in a dream. but if i actually have to face them, they'll see the failure. they'll see that everything i built was just a lie. i feel like there's no version of the future where i can just walk into a room and look them in the eye again. it feels like the only way to stop the humiliation is to just... not be there to face it.",
